title: 1994 Lancia Delta Integrale Evo
description: This Integrale Evo has a little less than 75,000 miles on the clock, but no matter. This one is the original with its original turbocharged 2.0-liter 16-valve engine under the hood making 215 horsepower. Built in 1993 and originally sold in Italy in 1994, a turbo timer, lightened hood, and aftermarket exhaust were added at one point. You can row your own on this Integrale Evoluzione II with a five-speed manual transmission that powers all four wheels. It even has air conditioning, praise be.
